      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The line between necessary social justice and harmful censorship is often blurred by those who wield power to silence dissent under the guise of progress. When a movement deplatforms individuals or labels them as \"dangerous\" solely for disagreeing, it crosses into authoritarianism and undermines the very freedom it claims to protect. The pursuit of progress becomes a problem when it prioritizes conformity over open debate, effectively turning a social movement into a tool for suppressing unpopular voices rather than advancing justice.",
